			<ns0:name>elijahtaylor@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/elijahtaylor@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The PDF viewer doesn't display external URLs in the status bar on hover.  The native viewer does.  Note that internal links, that is links that point in the current PDF, don't show up on the native viewer either.

Steps:
1) Find a PDF with embedded external links (e.g., http://www.hmohelp.ca.gov/testpage.pdf)
2) hover over an external link in the file
